{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "14", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "15", "S": "31"}}, "news": [{"title": "Waste charges stall Bengaluru apartments' property tax payments", "para": "Bengaluru apartment dwellers are delaying property tax payments due to confusion over solid waste management charges.  Complexes generating over 100kg of waste daily are eligible for exemption but face a complex declaration process. Residents lack data on waste generation and fear penalties for incorrect submissions, urging authorities for clearer guidelines and a simplified system.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/waste-charges-stall-bengaluru-apartments-property-tax-payments/130249759?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-132056/130249759.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Indore civic body gets cracking on illegal colonies, 16 row houses razed", "para": "The crackdown primarily focused on Zone 4. In Anjani Nagar, four row houses illegally constructed near a drain were completely removed, while at Jagdish Nagar in Banganga area, removal operations targeted 12 row houses. Officials revealed that six of them were nearly complete with finishing work underway, while the remaining six were under construction.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/indore-civic-body-gets-cracking-on-illegal-colonies-16-row-houses-razed/130249739?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-104456/130249739.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Gurugram: 10 years on, plot not handed over, Vatika told to pay \u20b962 lakh compensation", "para": "Allotees Vinay Kumar and Shalini Kumari booked a residential plot measuring 240 square yards in the developer's project 'Vatika India Next' located in Sector 85 in 2010. The total consideration value of the unit was recorded at Rs 62.7 lakh, with possession contractually promised by July 27, 2013.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/haryana-real-estate-authority-orders-vatika-ltd-to-compensate-homebuyers-62-lakh-for-delayed-plot-delivery/130249520?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-38444/130249520.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}]}